		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://markos.gaivo.net/blog/?p=72#comment-259</guid>
		<description>There is another reason for patents.

Patents encourage people to publish their ideas and to not keep them for themselves, e.G. not making corporate secrets from good ideas; because in the process of patenting you have to reveal the techniques etc.

This does, of course, not apply to things like internet advertisement - the technique is obvious at first sight.</description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>There is another reason for patents.</p>
<p>Patents encourage people to publish their ideas and to not keep them for themselves, e.G. not making corporate secrets from good ideas; because in the process of patenting you have to reveal the techniques etc.</p>
<p>This does, of course, not apply to things like internet advertisement &#8211; the technique is obvious at first sight.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
